<div class="container py-8">
  <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-4">Our tech stack</h1>
  <div class="flex flex-col gap-2">
    <p class="text-base">
      Technically the project is built using the lastest <a href="https://www.ruby-lang.org/" class="text-primary" target="_blank">Ruby</a>
      and <a href="https://rubyonrails.org/" class="text-primary" target="_blank">Rails</a> goodies such as
      <a href="https://hotwired.dev/" class="text-primary" target="_blank">Hotwire</a>,
      <a href="https://github.com/rails/solid_queue" class="text-primary" target="_blank">SolidQueue</a>,
      <a href="https://github.com/rails/solid_cache" class="text-primary" target="_blank">SolidCache</a>.
    </p>
    <p class="text-base">
      For the front end part we use <a href="https://vite.dev/" class="text-primary" target="_blank">Vite</a>,
      <a href="https://tailwindcss.com/" class="text-primary" target="_blank">Tailwind</a> with
      <a href="https://daisyui.com/" class="text-primary" target="_blank">Daisyui</a> components
      and <a href="https://stimulus.hotwire.dev/" class="text-primary" target="_blank">Stimulus</a>.
    </p>
    <p class="text-base">
      It is deployed on an <a href="https://hetzner.com/" class="text-primary" target="_blank">Hetzner</a>
      VPS with <a href="https://kamal-deploy.org/" class="text-primary" target="_blank">Kamal</a>
      using <a href="https://www.sqlite.org/" class="text-primary" target="_blank">SQlite</a> as the main database.
    </p>
    <p class="text-base">
      For compatible browsers it tries to demonstrate some of the possibilities of
      <a href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/API/View_Transitions_API" class="text-primary" target="_blank">Page View Transition API.</a>
    </p>
  </div>
</div>
